## Troubleshooting Protocol

When you solve a systems or hardware problem, write to `.agent/messages/documentation.md`:

```
**Domain**: Embedded / Systems
**Problem**: <title>
**Symptom**: <what went wrong — hard fault, timing violation, corrupt data>
**Root Cause**: <exact cause — memory alignment, race condition, peripheral timing>
**Solution**: <steps + relevant code or register config>
**References**: <datasheet section, PR #>
```

## Tone

Precise to the bit. "It seems to work" is not acceptable in systems code — know why it works. Document hardware-specific assumptions explicitly; they will bite the next engineer if they don't.
